# Mobile App (Expo) ‚Äî Setup & Implementation

**ALWAYS follow these when working in `mobile/`.**

## Reference Docs

- **Build guide:** `docs/MOBILE_APP_BUILD_GUIDE.md` ‚Äî dependencies, env, path aliases, CORS, errors
- **Plan:** `.cursor/plans/mobile_app_implementation_strategy.plan.md` ‚Äî phases, order, files
- **Design refs:** `docs/mobile-design-references.md` ‚Äî Revolut, Fuse patterns

## Dependencies

- Use `npx expo install <pkg>` for Expo packages (expo-secure-store, expo-router, expo-blur, etc.)
- Use `npm install` for non-Expo (axios, @tanstack/react-query, @gorhom/bottom-sheet)
- **DO NOT** add packages that require native code not in Expo Go unless using dev build

## Imports & Path Aliases

- Use `@/` alias: `import { api } from '@/services/api'`
- Requires `babel-plugin-module-resolver` + `tsconfig.json` paths (see build guide)
- Import order: 1) React/Expo, 2) services/hooks, 3) components, 4) constants

## API & Auth

- API URL: `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` or `Constants.expoConfig?.extra?.apiUrl`
- Token storage: `expo-secure-store` (not AsyncStorage for production)
- Same backend endpoints as web; reuse API structure from `Frontend/src/services/`

## Structure

- `app/` ‚Äî Expo Router file-based routes; `(tabs)/` for tab navigator
- `services/` ‚Äî api.ts, auth.ts
- `context/` ‚Äî AuthContext, ThemeContext
- `components/` ‚Äî reusable UI

## UI (React Native)

- Use React Native primitives: `View`, `Text`, `Pressable`, `ScrollView`, `FlatList`/`FlashList`
- **DO NOT** use shadcn/ui or web components ‚Äî they are for Frontend only
- Use `@expo/vector-icons` or `lucide-react-native` for icons

## Mobile ‚Äî In scope (build here when product needs it)

- **Tenant features:** Use `hasFeature('key')` from `useAuth()` with the same keys as web `FeatureRoute` in `Frontend/src/App.jsx` (e.g. `crm`, `products`, `paymentsExpenses`, `jobAutomation`, `orders`, `quoteAutomation`, `invoices`, `expenses`, `materials`, `leadPipeline`, `deliveries`). Hide menu entries and tab bar items when false; use `FeatureAccessDenied` on screens to block deep links.


- **Leads** ‚Äî pipeline / CRM leads (API `/leads`)
- **Tasks** ‚Äî workspace tasks (API `/user-workspace/tasks`)
- **Deliveries** ‚Äî delivery queue for completed jobs/sales (API `/deliveries`)

## Mobile App ‚Äî Out of Scope (Web Only)

**DO NOT implement these screens in the mobile app.** They are web-only; use the web app for these features.

- Platform admin (ABS Control Center / `/admin`)
- Automations
- Marketing
- Reports / analytics hubs
- Export data
- Pricing templates
- Vendors
- Employees
- Payroll
- Users / Team management
- Prescriptions (pharmacy)
- Drugs (pharmacy)
- Foot Traffic
- Accounting

## Rules from .cursorrules (Adapted)

- **No shadows** ‚Äî use borders, flat design
- **Primary color** #166534
- **Button order** ‚Äî secondary before primary
- **Business type** ‚Äî check `activeTenant?.businessType` for center tab action (Camera vs Plus)
- **Constants** ‚Äî define in `constants/` instead of magic strings
